{"tool":"sql_query","args":{"query":"WITH earliest_prod AS (SELECT lot_id, plant_code, line_id, shift, build_date, release_status FROM production_quality_measurements ORDER BY build_date ASC, lot_id ASC LIMIT 1), earliest_cal AS (SELECT calibration_id, platform_code, engine_family, production_release_date, fuel_map_revision, ecu_checksum FROM powertrain_calibration_specs ORDER BY production_release_date ASC, calibration_id ASC LIMIT 1) SELECT (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM production_quality_measurements WHERE build_date < (SELECT production_release_date FROM earliest_cal)) AS production_lots_earlier_than_earliest_calibration, ep.lot_id AS earliest_lot_id, ep.plant_code AS earliest_lot_plant_code, ep.line_id AS earliest_lot_line_id, ep.shift AS earliest_lot_shift, ep.build_date AS earliest_build_date, ep.release_status AS earliest_lot_release_status, ec.calibration_id AS earliest_calibration_id, ec.platform_code AS earliest_calibration_platform_code, ec.engine_family AS earliest_calibration_engine_family, ec.production_release_date AS earliest_calibration_release_date, ec.fuel_map_revision AS earliest_calibration_fuel_map_revision, ec.ecu_checksum AS earliest_calibration_ecu_checksum FROM earliest_prod ep CROSS JOIN earliest_cal ec","limit":10}}
{"answer":"Yes. There are 2 production lots with build_date earlier than the earliest calibration production_release_date. The comparison rows are: earliest production lot lot_id LOT-00053 (plant_code BER, line_id L2, shift B, build_date 2021-01-01, release_status HOLD) versus earliest calibration calibration_id CAL-0088 (platform_code PX-3, engine_family I4T, production_release_date 2021-01-03, fuel_map_revision FMR-2.7, ecu_checksum 0xA4F1C9D2). Since 2021-01-01 is earlier than 2021-01-03, at least one production lot is earlier than the earliest calibration release."}

